cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.NA 

The paper proposes and analyzes scalable algorithms for semi-supervised discriminant analysis, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The use of Krylov subspace methods and data sparsity suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-categories. The application of the proposed methods to an industry-scale data set for binary classification of compound activity on target proteins suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the use of large data sets and scalability suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
